      "date": "2013-03-17 04:58:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHmm, the failure is caused by this change,\r\n\r\n-        if (rc == 0 && mdd_sobj) {\r\n\r\n-                mdd_write_lock(env, mdd_sobj, MOR_SRC_CHILD);\r\n\r\n+       if (rc == 0 && mdd_sobj && mdd_spobj != mdd_tpobj) {\r\n\r\n+               mdd_write_lock(env, mdd_sobj,MOR_SRC_CHILD);\r\n\r\nEven the rename happens in the same directory, but the linkea(because of name change) needs to be update on the child as well. Unfortunately it also means this rename (rename remote dir under the same parent) will involve the cross-MDT operation as well, I will check whether it is doable for DNE phase I.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
